            <date when="1789">1789</date>
            <note>In his Preface, Williams noted that Mineralogy, although taught abroad, was neglected in British education. He aimed to bring his years of experience as a mining engineer to argue for the importance of mineral studies to 'this mining, manufacturing, and commercial country'.</note>
